@startuml IDEATION_PROCESS_v2

title **Architect's Design Process v2**\n(Hierarchical with Decisions, Parallelism, and Feedback Loops)\nPrequel to PROCESS_MAIN.puml

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam ArrowColor #333333
skinparam ActivityBorderColor #333333
skinparam ActivityFontColor #111111
skinparam NoteBackgroundColor #FFF9D6
skinparam NoteBorderColor #333333
skinparam PartitionBorderColor #999999
skinparam PartitionFontSize 14
skinparam DiamondBorderColor #333333
skinparam DiamondBackgroundColor #FFFDE7
skinparam DiamondFontSize 11

floating note left
  **Architect's Design Process**
  (Solo, Pre-Agent Ideation)
  ====
  **Output Truth Sources:**
  ""product/PRD.md"" = scope
  ""product/ARCH.md"" = arch
  ""product/contracts/*"" = APIs
  ----
  **Color Key:**
  <back:#D9ECFF>  Human design work  </back>
  <back:#FFF9D6>  Artifact output  </back>
  <back:#FFFDE7>  Decision gate  </back>
  <back:#DFF7E1>  Agent activity  </back>
  <back:#FFF2CC>  Gate milestone  </back>
  ----
  **Handoff:** /seed -> G0
  **Continues:** PROCESS_MAIN.puml
end note

start

' =============================================
' H1: WHAT & WHY — Sequential Foundation
' =============================================

partition "**H1: WHAT & WHY** (Problem Space)" #E8F4FD {

  :**Step 1: Vision & Value**
  ----
  Define business model, value
  proposition, and market fit.
  Identify core problem, target
  user, and why it matters.
  ----
  -> lean_canvas.pdf
  -> wardley_map.png; <<#D9ECFF>>

  note right
    **Lean Canvas** (Maurya)
    **Business Model Canvas**
    **Wardley Mapping**
    ----
    Output: **PRD.md S1**
  end note

  :**Step 2: Actors & Personas**
  ----
  Identify all actors: end users,
  system integrations, admin roles.
  Define goals, interaction channels
  (Web UI, API, CLI, mobile).
  ----
  -> personas.fig
  -> c4_context.drawio; <<#D9ECFF>>

  note right
    **User Personas** (Cooper)
    **Actor-Goal Lists** (UML)
    **C4 Context Diagram** (L1)
    ----
    Output: **PRD.md S1-2**
    + **ARCH.md S4** (trust)
  end note

  :**Step 3: Scope Boundaries**
  ----
  In-scope (MVP), out-of-scope,
  deferred to V2+. Constraints:
  budget, timeline, compliance.
  ----
  -> scope_matrix.md; <<#D9ECFF>>

  note right
    **MoSCoW** Prioritization
    **Kano Model**
    **TOGAF Arch Vision**
    ----
    Output: **PRD.md S2**
  end note

  :Artifacts: **PRD.md S1-2**
  Vision + Actors + Scope; <<#FFF9D6>>
}

' =============================================
' H2: LOGICAL DESIGN — Fan-Out After Stories
' =============================================

partition "**H2: LOGICAL DESIGN** (Decomposition & Flows)" #F0F7E6 {

  :**Step 4: Use Case Modeling**
  ----
  Map all system use cases. Group
  by functional area using UC tags
  (UC:SEARCH, UC:INGEST, UC:AUTH).
  Establish functional topology
  and service boundaries.
  ----
  -> diagrams/use_cases.puml
  -> event_storm.png
  -> context_map.png; <<#D9ECFF>>

  note right
    **UML Use Case Diagrams**
    **DDD Bounded Contexts**
    **Event Storming** (Brandolini)
    ----
    Output: **PRD.md S5** UC Tags
  end note

  :**Step 5: Story Decomposition**
  ----
  Break use cases into vertical
  slices (S-V###), each <=1 day.
  Acceptance via Given/When/Then.
  Risk tags: LOW / MED / HIGH.

  **Scrum -> Process Steward:**
  Theme = strategic (not tracked)
  Epic  = UC tag (label only)
  Story = S-V### (PRD.md S4)
  Task  = T-V###.## (JIT, agent)
  ----
  -> story_map.png; <<#D9ECFF>>

  note right
    **User Story Mapping** (Patton)
    **INVEST** criteria
    **Gherkin** Given/When/Then
    ----
    Output: **PRD.md S4** Backlog
  end note

  fork

    :**Step 6: Requirements**
    **(FR + NFR)**
    ----
    FRs = stories (Step 5).
    NFRs: latency, throughput,
    uptime, security, observability.
    ----
    -> PRD.md S3 (tables); <<#D9ECFF>>

    note left
      **Quality Attribute Scenarios**
      **12-Factor App**
      **OWASP Top 10** (security NFRs)
      ----
      Output: **PRD.md S3**
      + **ARCH.md S1** Constraints
    end note

  fork again

    :**Step 7: User Journeys & UI**
    ----
    Trace happy-path per actor.
    Design info hierarchy and
    component structure. Select
    frontend tech stack.
    ----
    -> user_flows.fig
    -> wireframes.fig
    -> component_tree.drawio; <<#D9ECFF>>

    note right
      **User Journey Maps**
      **Atomic Design** (Frost)
      **Wireframing** (low-fi)
      ----
      Output: **product/diagrams/**
      Refines **PRD.md S4** acceptance
    end note

  end fork

  if (NFRs invalidate\narchitecture\nassumptions?) then (yes)
    :Revise use cases and
    stories to align with
    performance/scale
    constraints;
    note right
      **Feedback Loop**
      Return to Step 4-5.
      NFR constraints may force
      scope reduction or story
      re-sequencing.
    end note
    -[#FF6600,dashed]->
  else (no)
  endif

  if (Frontend\nneeded?) then (yes)
    :Include frontend in
    architecture scope.
    Wireframes from Step 7
    drive component design.;
  else (API only)
    :Backend-only scope.
    No UI components
    in architecture.;
  endif

  :Artifacts: **PRD.md S3-5**
  Stories + Requirements + UC Tags
  + **product/diagrams/** (UI); <<#FFF9D6>>
}

' =============================================
' H3: PHYSICAL DESIGN — Architecture First,
'     Then Three Parallel Tracks
' =============================================

partition "**H3: PHYSICAL DESIGN** (Architecture, Data, Cloud, APIs)" #FFF8E8 {

  :**Step 8: Architecture (C4)**
  ----
  Design at three zoom levels:
  Context (actors + externals),
  Container (services, DBs, MQs),
  Component (modules in each
  container). Record key ADRs.
  ----
  -> diagrams/c4_*.puml; <<#D9ECFF>>

  note right
    **C4 Model** (Simon Brown)
    **Hexagonal Architecture**
    (Ports & Adapters)
    **ADRs** (Nygard format)
    ----
    Output: **ARCH.md S4** (C4-lite)
    + **ARCH.md S1** (ADR principles)
  end note

  if (Monolith or\ndistributed?) then (distributed)
    :Multi-service architecture.
    Define service boundaries,
    API gateways, message queues,
    separate data stores.;
  else (monolith)
    :Single-service MVP.
    Modular monolith with
    clean internal boundaries.
    Defer splitting to V2+.;
  endif

  ' --- Three parallel tracks after architecture ---

  fork

    ' Track A: Tech Stack (independent)
    :**Step 9: Tech Stack**
    ----
    Select technology for every
    layer: frontend, backend, DB,
    cache, auth, CI/CD, monitoring,
    IaC. Each choice is an ADR.
    ----
    -> tech_comparison_matrix; <<#D9ECFF>>

    note left
      **Technology Radar**
      (ThoughtWorks)
      **TOGAF Tech Architecture**
      **12-Factor App**
      ----
      Output: **ARCH.md S2**
    end note

  fork again

    ' Track B: Data -> API (sequential)
    :**Step 10: Data Model (ERD)**
    ----
    Design entities, relationships,
    constraints, indexes. Define
    Pydantic models as DTO source
    of truth (extra="forbid").
    ----
    -> diagrams/erd.puml
    -> contracts/schemas.py; <<#D9ECFF>>

    note right
      **ERD** (Chen / Crow's Foot)
      **DDD Aggregates**
      **Pydantic StrictModel**
      ----
      Output: **contracts/schemas.py**
    end note

    :**Step 11: API Design**
    ----
    Define HTTP API: endpoints,
    methods, schemas, error envelope,
    cursor pagination, auth scheme.
    OpenAPI spec written BEFORE code.
    **Schemas from Step 10 feed
    directly into OpenAPI components.**
    ----
    -> contracts/openapi.yaml; <<#D9ECFF>>

    note right
      **Contract-First Design**
      **RESTful Guidelines**
      **Cursor Pagination**
      ----
      Output: **contracts/openapi.yaml**
      Every endpoint traces to
      >= 1 story in PRD.md S4
    end note

  fork again

    ' Track C: Cloud -> Security (sequential)
    :**Step 12: Cloud Architecture**
    ----
    Design deployment: compute
    (Fargate, Cloud Run), networking
    (VPC, ALB, CDN), data (RDS,
    ElastiCache), observability,
    CI/CD pipeline, IaC strategy.
    ----
    -> diagrams/cloud_arch.*; <<#D9ECFF>>

    note left
      **Well-Architected Framework**
      (5 pillars: OpEx, Security,
      Reliability, Perf, Cost)
      **IaC** (Terraform/Pulumi)
      **GitOps** for deploys
      ----
      Output: **ARCH.md S4** (topology)
      + **ARCH.md S6** (extensions)
    end note

    :**Step 13: Security & Compliance**
    ----
    Define auth (JWT, OAuth2),
    authorization (RBAC/ABAC),
    data classification (PII),
    secrets management, threat
    model (top 3 attack vectors).
    **Cloud topology from Step 12
    shapes secrets management.**
    ----
    -> diagrams/threat_model; <<#D9ECFF>>

    note left
      **OWASP Top 10**
      **STRIDE** threat modeling
      **Data Classification**
      (public/internal/confidential)
      ----
      Output: **ARCH.md S7** Security
    end note

  end fork

  if (Threat model requires\nnew auth/RBAC stories?) then (yes)
    :Add security stories
    to PRD.md S4 Backlog.
    Update risk tags and
    story sequence.;
    note right
      **Feedback Loop**
      Security analysis (Step 13)
      generates new stories that
      feed back to PRD.md S4.
      May affect Step 5 scope.
    end note
    -[#FF6600,dashed]->
  else (no)
  endif

  :Artifacts: **ARCH.md S1-7**
  + **contracts/** (schemas.py,
  openapi.yaml)
  + **product/diagrams/** (C4,
  ERD, cloud, threat model); <<#FFF9D6>>
}

' =============================================
' HANDOFF: Distillation with Validation Loop
' =============================================

partition "**HANDOFF** (Distillation & Agent Initialization)" #F5F0FF {

  repeat

    :**Step 14: Artifact Distillation**
    ----
    Consolidate all design outputs.
    Cross-validate consistency:

    **Checks:**
    - OpenAPI paths match Pydantic
      (names, types, optionality)
    - Every endpoint traces to
      >= 1 story in PRD.md S4
    - ARCH repo map matches actual
      directory structure
    - pyproject.toml deps match
      ARCH.md S2 tech stack
    ----
    **Final Artifact Set:**
    1. product/PRD.md (S1-7)
    2. product/ARCH.md (S1-7)
    3. contracts/openapi.yaml
    4. contracts/schemas.py
    5. contracts/CONTRACTS.md
    6. product/diagrams/*; <<#D9ECFF>>

  backward :Consistency check FAILED.\nReturn to affected step:\n- Story/endpoint mismatch -> Step 5\n- Schema/OpenAPI drift -> Step 10-11\n- Repo structure mismatch -> Step 8;

  repeat while (All consistency\nchecks pass?) is (no) not (yes)

  :All artifacts committed to repo
  ----
  **product/PRD.md** = scope truth
  **product/ARCH.md** = arch truth
  **product/contracts/** = APIs
  **product/diagrams/** = visuals; <<#FFF9D6>>

  :**Step 15: Execute /seed**
  ----
  Human runs **/seed** command.
  Triggers Phase P0 (Install
  and Wire). Explicit handoff
  from architect to agent.

  **What follows (PROCESS_MAIN):**
  /plan (P1-P4) refines w/ human
  /next (P5-P7) builds per story
  /release (P8-P11) hardens; <<#D9ECFF>>

  :**Agent Activates at P0**
  ----
  Read: PRD.md, ARCH.md,
  contracts/*, PROGRESS.md
  Validate all artifacts exist.
  Run ""make check"" (baseline).
  Log evidence in PROGRESS.md.
  If PASS: record G0 = PASS.
  If FAIL: log Issues (I-###).
  ----
  Development process begins.
  See: **PROCESS_MAIN.puml**; <<#DFF7E1>>

  :**Gate G0 -- Installed**
  (artifacts exist + check runnable)
  ----
  **PROCESS_MAIN.puml starts here**
  /plan -> /next -> /release; <<#FFF2CC>>

}

stop

@enduml
